caption: Asked to reserve a table with a female at the front and was told they do not do reservations. Come back an hour later and to find out there is a wait list. Very disappointing, was not offered the opportunity to get on the wait list. Was really looking forward to trying this place, bad customer service.

Excellent, fresh food! I enjoyed beautifully prepared vegetables and plump juicy shrimp in my dishes while my husband has a fabulous beef dish in true szechuan style. Friend enjoyed their vegan “chicken” as well. Dumplings and bao were also delicious. Highly recommended!

wish i could give a better star rating overall service was quick and great, friendly staff and string beans were delicious as well as the rice but i ordered chicken and broccoli and it tasted spoiled was disappointed and the manager apologized as well as the waiter,  but understandable because it was the end of the night, hopefully I’ll be able to come back i guess being from new york gives higher expectations but overall i’d recommend it

Crawfish and crab dumpling are soooooo good. We love on the northshore but the drive is soo worth it. The food and dumplings are to die for. Also it’s such a rare find!

Authentic Chinese food in NOLA. The soup dumplings taste exactly like the beet I ever had in NYC. Great service and fast cook times.

EXCELLENT. Truly the best Chinese restaurant in New Orleans. Authentic, delicious, and great service. MUST try the Xiaolongbao.

Authentic and delicious! Excellent service. They have some great vegan options, and were able to make some dishes into vegan ones upon request! Highly recommended!
Delicious dinner! Best wonton soup I've ever had! Great service, too!

Excellent service and addictive food.  Will be making more trips to the quarter from central city just for their food.

A place we really wanted to try, but could never get into, what with the pandemic. Even with the pandemic, it was a very popular place. We did get in by going early for dinner. Even early, the place was frenetic, pickup orders flying out the door, people coming to dine in, the staff was flying. We ordered, got our food in a reasonable time given how busy they were, and it was entirely worth it. I had seafood noodle soup, my wife had shrimp and eggplant, and we shared bao. Food was excellent!
The food was very fresh and authentic. The service is always good. I visit often and recommend this restaurant to others.

Really good restaurant with great prices and delicious food. Environment is clean an charming. Our waiter was polite and friendly. Food was great and portions are humongous. Plus they have small fish pond by the entrance. Loved that place
Amazing food, okay service. the food is so good, but I’d recommend ordering takeout.

Wait was 45mins to an hour wait. But I handled it by just walking around the French Quaters. Getting a snack might be the way. Food was good. Service was good. Something to definitely try for the 1st time.
Consistently the best Chinese food I’ve ever had, every time is a treat. This place is a real gem.

Great experience in this restaurant. The food was great. Server was friendly. Everything was great and love the place. I recommend everyone to visit this place once when you are in New Orleans. It was worth being here. The price was also quiet affordable.
Food...Delicious! Service...Outstanding! We waited 45 minutes for a table. It was well worth the wait.

Best Dim Sum! My wontons had whole shrimp in them. The wonton soup had plenty of flavor. My second time here and I would come back again for sure! Not your typical chinese restaurant. It's small and they have lots of pick up orders. Its worth waiting for.
Good place to enjoy Taiwanese food. Liked the xiaolongbao and the stirred fried XO noodle and the shrimp fried rice. The popcorn chicken was okay.
The food was great and the portions were satisfying. Would love to come back.

My wife and I absolutely loved this place. Being locals we have went multiple times. The Xiao Long Bao are our favorite...highly recommend. With that said I am making this review after the pandemic and getting take out which was okay. Not the same as eating in the restaurant but what take out is. If your looking for great Chinese food in the quarter, this is your place.

A colleague and a friend (both from Hong Kong) strongly recommended this restaurant to me right after I moved here. Therefore, I had very high expectations toward it. This afternoon I was finally able to try it with my colleague. I have to say, they very much disappointed me -  The Jianbing almost had no taste (even with the crawfish in it). This is absurd! How could even the crawfish taste so plain?!  The Pan-fried tiny bao SHOULD have some meat soup in it (even the instant ones I bought from Asia grocery store tasted better after unfrozen), but didn’t.  The Phoenix claws were okay, about average compared to the ones I had in the Chinatown of nyc or chicago (not to mention the authentic ones I had in China).  After being so disappointed by the first three dishes, I totally lost appetite and did not want to try the crabmeat & crawfish Bao. If these turned out to be great, I will update here.  I don’t know how this restaurant got such a high online rating - 4.7 out of 5!!! Given the food I got today, there must be something wrong... could it be they changed the chef temporarily? Or the chef caught COVID (thus lost taste)? Really have no idea.

(Translated by Google) Online order. Demanding, catch-specific, practical boxes. Overall, the items are excellent. Texture, spice, rich presence of fillings, one by one. - Japanese fried dumplings with chicken, 4pcs-a little thick noodles, but can withstand the catch; - China doufu egg-vegetable-dumpling soup, with 6 dumplings-many and delicious; - Korean chicken and vegetable bao, 3pcs-perfect; - Thai mango and pineapple Sweet dumplings, 2pcs - a very pleasant sweet experience with crumbly, crumbly noodles, its filling is not intrusively sweet. - Sweet and sour sauce, Korean hot sauce-harmoniously fitting supplement with great taste. At a price point, something could be grated, especially on the soup front, but it still represents a particularly recommended level.  (Original) Netes rendelés. Igényes, fogás-specifikus, praktikus dobozok. A tételekről összességében elmondható, hogy kiválóan voltak elkészítve. Állag, fűszerezés, töltelékek gazdag jelenléte, egytől egyig. - Japán sült gombóc csirkével, 4db-egy kicsit vastag tészta, de elbírja a fogás; - Kina doufu tojas-zöldség-gombóc leves, 6db gombóccal-sok és finom; - Koreai csirke és zöldség bao, 3db-tökéletes; - Thai mangó és ananász Édes gombóc, 2db -nagyon kellemes édes tapasztalás porhanyós, omlós tésztája kitűnő, tölteléke nem tolakodóan édes. - Édes-savanyú mártás, koreai forró szósz-harmónikusan passzoló kiegészítő, remek ízvilággal. Árfekvésen lehetne valamicskét reszelni főleg leves fronton, de így is különösen ajánlott szintet képvisel.
AUTHENTIC!!! WOW WEEEE!! I LOVE THIS SPOT! A must eat at restaurant!!! We have only been here once, but it was off the Chain!!! A+

Loved the crawfish crabmeat bao!
The food is absolutely amazing, some of the best xiao long bao I’ve ever had and a great take NOLA take on it, Crawfish and Crabmeat Xiao Long Bao

The flavors and the manner in which the food is made is both familiar enough and different enough to make this a worthwhile effort.  This is NOT your regular Chinese restaurant. Unbelievable quality and tastes like actual food you find in China. Very good and fresh all around. So glad i found this place. Deliver via postmates, its worth it.
Best Chinese food in the STATE!! Be prepared to wait because the line to get in is always long but I promise it’s worth it.
Great dumplings. I really enjoyed this place and would like to try some of their other entree's.

I visited New Orleans in February 2020. I was skeptical but my daughter assured me that they had a gluten free menu options. I had a delicious gluten free meal-including gluten free noodles—and it was delicious and had no problems later!!! The rest of my family ordered lots of dumplings and loved them as well! Great food awesome service nice environment
Excellent. Great food and servicr

The food is great! I had to wait a while (didn't know you could make reservations on Yelp) but it was worth it. A bit of advice though, if it's your first time there make your reservation after you park 😁
Best food ever anywhere

Came back for the third time In a week. It’s been cold and I started to feel kinda ick.  Came in had hot tea and the hot and sour soup. I’m allergic to shellfish. The hot and sour soup is also spicy hot.  It took a minute for it to work. But I feel like I had a week on antibiotics. Woo My sinuses are all cleaned out.  Awesome
I want to keep going here to try the whole menu. It's really delicious.
Delicious dumplings. The soup dumplings were a little larger than I'm used too but still tasty. We will be back on our next visit.
So good! And not a bad price point. We had the beef noodle soup, lane bao, spicy dumplings and pan fried pot stickers. Everything was delicious!

Most of the time I come here, the food is always amazing. One advice would be to lower the amount of vegetable in the pork dumpling cause it feels like 7:3 filling of vegetable and meat. Only once when I order soup dumping, it comes out flat and not soupy but I still ate it because the place was busy. Other than that the service is pretty good, workers are very friendly and active, and sitting back with their tea and sipping it, is an experience to enjoy.

Fabulous chinese food with authentic & rich flavors. Service was good; however, they do deliver dishes to the table as they are finished and piping hot - so not everyone gets their dishes at the same time. Relax and enjoy the wait. It's worth it!

I like this place quite a but, but it tends to be overcrowded and that stresses the staff noticeably.
Service was amazing! And food was really good. As a local,  I will certainly be back

I had ordered the stewed beef noodle soup. My companion had ordered the house spicy seafood soup. The soups were outstanding. The broths were well balanced and the beef was tender. I would definitely recommend this place to my friends.
Amazing authentic Chinese and Dim Sum!

Very delightful. A friend and I split and enjoyed all 3 items we ordered.  All had a fresh sense about them.  The Garlic Shrimp was out entree.  The place was busy and a bit noisy, but it is certainly worth another visit!
The food was excellent.

Tried to eat here X2, first time they closed early for Chinese New Year and second time the wait time was too long - so ordered take out X2. Was a little tired of USA food after 2 weeks of driving in the Southern States.  I think this place is very popular with locals, and everyone in the queue would rave about how good it is. As a Chinese who has eaten Chinese food in New York and at home in London, I would say the quality from a purely Chinese perspective is variable.  The steamed 蟹粉小笼包 were not bad at all and would recommend. The plain rice is American long grain so it's so so. The sea food fried rice was not good. The garlic pea shoots were fine. I can make better hot and sour soup at home. They ran out one night of the stir fried spicy cabbage, so kindly substituted for pea shoots. I was told this dish contains pork, which I thought would have been fine for flavour, but obviously not something you'd find in 手撕包菜 it in fact it contains extremely salty bacon in large pieces. I recognise my dish did not have the intended cabbage, but there is no way that would have been nice either. The bacon made the entire dish salty beyond belief and far too meaty to enjoy. Would have been better without meat altogether. The green beans weren't good and smothered in sweet sauce.  So in summary, I think this place is fine for people who do not know what good Chinese food is and what it's supposed to taste like, but not great for an actual Chinese person. However, if you're craving a change from the usual USA and Cajun fare, I think it's in a great location and it is certainly very edible. I will end on the fact the xiao long bao are pretty good.

Very unique and we'll prepared Chinese.  Different from most, as the dishes did not have sweet sticky sauces.  The Bao shrimp and crawfish dumplings we're good, as was the five spice ribs.  Garlic shrimp and Won Ton soup were also good.  Nice change of pace and a lot of choices.
Amazing food. Great Service. Miguel is a great server everything that he recommended was fantastic!

I love everything about this place. Somehow I get a parking spot right outside the door on 9/10 visits. We are well past our 15th visit and we're it not for a goal to eat more at home that number would be double. We take everyone here, we go alone, we wait with others, though we are mindful of the wait and try to go early on weeknights to avoid it. Wings, bao, noodles, cake, buckwheat tea. Five star is not enough for this place - the beef noodle soup is otherworldly and the popcorn chicken, xian long bao and veggies are as authentic as what you’d have in Taiwan. Oh and the service is great!

First time for my husband and I. I ordered the seafood soup and my husband got the Tso chicken. The seafood soup was good but very disappointed in how over cooked the crawfish was. It was crawfish jerky with know flavor. Now the shrimp and octopus was great but what I didn't get though was the noodles not being rice noodles. Literally spaghetti noodles. Ive cooked enough to know that those were spaghetti noodles. For my husband's dish the chicken  was good. Nice heat to it but we both agreed the broccoli was off and even the broccoli in my soup tasted off. My husband said it tasted like its stored next to seafood. Either way tasted off.

I had a couple friends that hyped me up for this restaurant. I can only say for myself that this place is okay. It's a little pricey but then again, there aren't any dumpling restaurants I know of in the area. We ordered Shu Mai, Basil Popcorn chicken, Bok Choy, steamed Pork Bao, Hot & Sour dumpling soup & Xiao Long Bao (Soup dumplings). My favorite was the hot & sour dumpling soup because it had really good flavor. Everything else was okay, the Xiao Long Bao kept tearing apart so the soup would just spill out before I can get it on my plate which was a little disappointing. I may give this place another try because the service was really good compared to some of the food.

Stumbled upon this place while walking around French Quarter-  There was a wait to be seated but that’s usually a good indication. So glad we waited. We couldn’t get enough of their  family recipe chili paste so much we ordered it to go. Be warned - it’s very spicy but oh so good. Wish they would sell it online. Would be going back for sure!

This place. Yummo. If I were to die tomorrow, I would want that spicy fiery bacon cabbage as part of my last supper. Seriously yall, I don't know what they do to it, but I can't get enough of it... It is lovingly referred to as crack cabbage in my house. All the other stuff is amazing. Ive been there a few times now and have really not ventured into the main meals because I go crazy with the dim sum. Bring friends. Try all the things. It's not China town NYC but it's damn fine.
Excellent quick and friendly service. Largish portions and great flavors. Had the hot n sour, broccoli, fried rice. Friend had popcorn chicken and loved it. Plenty of good vegetarian options.
I will come back often for the salt and pepper squid! It is really really tasty! I also got some soup dumplings. This place is one of my spots now.
Authentic dim sum

Honestly this was one of the best meals we've had in our many trips to New Orleans.  When you need a break from the amazing cajun and creole spots, try out this spectacular dim sum spot.  Do not come here without ordering the stuffed chinese crepes.   We are still talking about them months after and this will be a spot we hit up multiple times on our next trip.

Did not disappoint.  Very accurate production of traditional flour based selections.  FRESHLY steamed in house prepared to your table.  6 of us at table enjoyed shrimp crepe, small meat filled steam buns (小龍包), wonton soup better than hot and Sour Soup. Beef soup noodle reminds me of the 'beef stew noodles' in Kim's Restaurant at Four Columns in Harvey, good. ShuMai (燒賣) OK.  Egg plant dish and beef dish have similar sauce. Somehow, I forgot to order boiled dumplings which looked steamingly fantastic coming to next tables. Dessert OK.  Will be back.  Line outside waiting to come in was long at 7:45pm on Sunday.
The best new restaurant in the Quarter. Prepare to wait for a table. They got real popular real quick. 12 clams and you got you a meal.

One of my new favorite restaurants in the French Quarter. Since its opening, the restaurant has been a huge success and it's evident in the continuous quality of food and service. Eveything is made fresh and to order, so don't go in in a rush. Good quality food takes time! Everything on the menu is amazing!!! I recommend this restaurant to everyone.

This new little place is amazing! It's not your run of the mill Chinese place. They serve a wide variety of dumplings and other dim sum items that are all made with love. The soup dumplings are full of delicious broth and the juicy tiny bao have the most perfect crisp bottoms. The crepes are sweet and filled with crisp lettuce and fresh meats. The steamed bao are sublime, fluffy and light. This is a family owned and run business. Everyone really cares about the food and the experience. Make sure to call ahead to get on the waiting list, because on Sundays you can wait for over an hour. But even if you forget to call, it will be worth the wait!

Had the soup dumplings, the beef roll, and the pan fried pork dumplings. Everything was fresh and super tasty. The beef roll and pan fried dumplings were the best, and the soup dumplings came in 3rd. Service was great, ask for Teresa she was awesome!

This is the best authentic Chinese food in this whole area. Anyone who gave less than 5-stars was due to personal problems, service wait times or price. But the food is DELICIOUS. For the stir fries,  they are all spicy and come with a side of steamed rice. But like others said, if you want a table, get there right as they open at 3pm. Or you can order by phone, then just pick it up in 45 mins.
Dim Sum - yum!
This place was SOOOOOO GOOD!

The food is delicious with obvious attention to detail. Things were a bit pricey for Dim Sum, and the location is small so expect a wait if you don't arrive at opening. Given it's in the French Quarter, these factors should be expected. Overall satisfied with the meal and would definitely consider going back if I don't want to venture to the Westbank.
Great food. Friendly staff.
Food is amazing. Service is terrible.  Ut the food is so good it doesnt even matter that the servers have no clue how to wait tables. They need a good manager that stays on the floor with them.
Great service and amazing food (especially the dumplings and noodles). Had a 30 min wait which was fine. Most authentic Chinese restaurant I've been to in the city.

An absolute must visit. Forget red beans and rice (no disrespect) but this place is a gem in the French Quarter. Some of the most authentic Chinese food I’ve had in a long time and since visiting Chinese some years ago. A chic little spot, cozy atmosphere, and friendly stuff. Also, all bao and dumplings are handmade to order.
Great place to eat
On our recent trip to New Orleans we had a great dinner here, despite some small miscommunications. The food was excellent, and the service was great, I would definitely recommend!
Best Chinese in the city, San Francisco style.
The food was really good and the service was great!

This place is so popular that you have to get there when the doors open at 3pm to be assured a seat without a wait. We bought extra dishes to take home. The egg roll are delish as were the dumplings. I had a stewed beef crepe which was a treat. Also had a noodle and shrimp, chicken and veggies dish which was perfect. My wife had a mango smoothie which was delicious. The service was perfect  and the food came out piping hot. The t-shirts the staff wore Had a cute Chinese/New Orleans slogan. "Who Gao Dat" and the restaurant logo on the back. I bought one to remember the fine meal. Reasonably priced and you can not go wrong. A great break from the heavy; deep-fried local fare and two blocks from our home.
Absolutely amazing. Definitely worth the wait.
Good chinese food. Friendly staff. Fair price for serving.

This was my first time having dim sum. The food was amazing. And the service is excellent. They take the time to even show you how to properly eat it I would love to definitely have it again if I come back to New Orleans

Service was painfully slow.  When I asked about our order after a 40 minute wait our server said the chef was fulfilling a huge take out order ahead of us.  Then got the food ten minutes later but everything was doused in cayenne.  If you go, be very patient and definitely don't complain about anything.
We really needed this restaurant in the French Quarter. Everything here is great, and we haved most of the menu. Just fantastic!
I am impressed that I could meet these kind of quility chinese dishes in New Orleans. Loved it and worth to wait!!!
Lovely lovely food. Try not to over order .. but you will anyway.  The walnut shrimp are great but then so is everything.  Take cash.
Don’t miss the Jian Bing!
Amazing food.  Usually there is a waiting time to be seated, but trust me, it is really worth the wait.  I go there at least twice a week.
Stewed beef soup was the best I've ever had!
Food was good but the service was crazyy slow

Very authentic, good Cantonese cuisine. The mounted  TV's are an unnecessary distraction, and the party music is a little loud bouncing around against the hard surfaces inside the room. The service staff is very nice, if a little too busy to be attentive, but they do try. The kitchen still seems to be working out a system because the food service delivery was a little slow. Will positively return. Well worth the attention of anyone looking for authentic Cantonese style food.
Great food, great service, worth the wait. Dim sum selection not huge but what they do have is very good. Must trys are the spicy wontons, the crab & crawfish soup Dumplings, and the Chinese crepe.
Love the soup dumplings and the popcorn chicken and fried calamari 😋
Excellent food, worth the wait

Visited this spot while waiting for a parade, there was a bit of wait because of the night but it was well worth it. The dumplings were delicious and me and my partner's entrees were amazing. It tasted great and was a great way to start the evening.
Love the chicken with string beans, the fried rice is a little oily.
D-lishious!!!! Had the pork soup dumplings and the best chicken fried rice ever.  We will be back as much as we can.
Lots of yummy options you can't find anywhere else. Also soup dumplings that don't tear as soon as you try to remove them from the lining of the bamboo steamer!

Hardly to find Restaurant specialized in serving BAO. Dian Xin is the best choice in town. Service is good. Popcorn chicken is a must try. And their hot tea. Can’t find anywhere else. Highly recommend!!

A friend (local) suggested this place. I wasn’t disappointed. My server was very helpful with menu suggestions and prompt with service. I was asked by 2 other staff if I was ready to order (after I already had) so they appear to have taken the service criticism to heart. With seating for 35-40 it’s not gonna take many to fill it up, but any wait is worth it. Will definitely eat here again.
Food was awesome.  Service was really slow but everyone was nice.  Hopefully it'll improve once they've been open for a little longer.  I'd definitely go back again!

Anyone that is complaining needs to realize that this business just opened, are extremely busy, and are working out the kinks. If you don't want to wait, go as soon as they open. But absolutely go, because Dian Xin is incredible. I spent some time living in Hong Kong and this place is the real deal. The soup dumplings are perfect. No matter what you get it's made with care. Support this business!
The best Chinese kitchen I have ever tried!!! Everything was wonderful and delicious! 100% recommended!!! Thank you!!!
Joints super on point 👌🏿

It’s very, very good.  They have just been overwhelmed with customers, and it was unexpected. There was a review and article that went around the Internet and the local newspapers that really put them on the map. And consequently it’s drawing usually large crowds.  They seem to have eliminated the lunch. They don’t open till 3 PM. They had to adjust their ordering to have enough food. They’ve only been open a few days. Give them time to settle in. 😊👍❤️🎈 🇨🇳 🇨🇳

Great authentic Chinese food. Lovely family run restaurant. My group ordered 8 different dishes and they were all excellent.
Great authentic Chinese food! Dim sum and then some.

This is the best Chinese restaurant in New Orleans and frankly I could leave it at that but let's dig in. I went on a Sunday afternoon right as they were opening (3pm) with a large group (7). We arrived around 2:40 and there was already a line forming. We were seated right away and the service was attentive but chaotic. We ordered everything at once basically but it came out sporadically. The dishes we got (and my opinion) *Five Spice Fried Pork Ribs - fine, could use more spice to cut through the grease *Salt & Pepper Squid - same as above *Xiao Long Bao - very good *Crabmeat and Crawfish Bao - not as good as the xiao long bao but a really great local take on the dish. Will surely become a restaurant special *Pork and Shrimp Dumplings - whether fried or steamed they had a great flavor, the mince meat was well seasoned. *Sauteed snow pea tips with garlic - have to have something healthy. Pretty good *Stir Friend Noodles in XO Sauce - good. Much better then the takeout lo mein you may be used to *Walnut Shrimp - excellent *Beef Eggplant - showstopper. An absolutely delicious dish - perfectly balanced spice and tender eggplant. I'd come back for this. *Salted Fish Chicken Fried Rice - delicious. Definitely recommend trying something outside your comfort zone.  With the food out of the way let's address the elephant in the room - service. It's not great. You're probably going to have to wait to get a table, you're gonna have to wait to get food and it will arrive randomly. The above described menu probably took over an hour to fully arrive and it did not come in any predictable way. This is pretty much why they lose a star. That being said - they're brand new! I don't even know why people are flocking here. I think once they hire more staff and figure out the kinks that every restaurant has at the beginning they'll be a true 5 star destination. I already can't wait to go back.  I see lot of people referring to it as a dim sum restauraunt and while they serve a lot of dim sum staples don't expect a dim sum like experience - that is bringing a large group and sharing a lot of plates. It's definitely geared towards smaller group dining. The "mains" are definitely  individual entrees. I think this would be a great spot to go with 2-4 people and share some appetizers and get individual dishes.  Finally - yes it's in the quarter so don't try to drive here. You won't find parking. Take a streecar/Lyft/Uber/bike or something.

Great potential. Xiao long bao (soup dumplings) was very good, maybe needs a little more liquid and little less meat, but the flavors were great. The pork buns were good as well as the shrimp noodle dish and fried rice. I do NOT recommend szechuan beef dish, unless they fix the recipe- it was way too oily and the beef was soft and flavorless. It reminded me of a cheap strip mall Chinese restaurant dish. Will be back and look forward to sampling other dishes. Staff was friendly and responsive.

Great, Amazing Food, but Horrible customer service. We were there Sat. January 26th. We understand the wait time to get a table, (1 hour), once we were seated, they took our drink order. We got so wrapped up in talking we didn't notice that after 1 hour and 45 minutes, at the table, that nobody had taken our food order. We left.... Waited a total of 2 hours and 45 minutes and still no food order. If you going to eat here, please order by phone. Service is atrocious
Amazing food and amazing service!!! Would 10/10 recomend. Im gonna send all my friends here! No doubt
Exactly what was needed in Nola. Thank the Lord there is good dim sum in the Big Easy!!
THE absolute, hands down, BEST Chinese food I have had in New Orleans, if not the entire South!!!  Not to be missed.  -a satisfied New Yorker

Recieved a door flyer from them. Tried to order for over an hour. They never answered either of their phones. They won't last long at this rate. ZERO customer service is no way to endear yourself to the locals in the Quarter.

HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE I’m a New Orleans local, and when I heard the news about an authentic Chinese restaurant opening in the quarter I was beyond excited. So, this past Saturday my wife and I decided to go give it a try. Traffic was pretty bad and we got there a little later than expected, around 2:15PM. We saw that they close at 3, but there was only a short line with a few people in front of us so we thought maybe we’re okay. Then comes the waiting game. 35 minutes later at 2:50PM, a waitress came out and rudely inform us and the people lining behind us that they would not be able to serve us. So we just waited 35 minutes for nothing. I know they close at 3, but I don’t understand why they waited until literally 10 minutes before the closing time to inform the customers. I mean there are so many things that could’ve been done to avoid this, hiring a hostress, taking numbers, or even using one of those phone apps that send text messages to waiting customers. By doing none of that and just having people lining up until the last minute really shows how much this restaurant cares about their customers. I honestly think they’re taking advantage of customers in line to create some type of hype to draw in more attentions. We will not be revisiting. There are plenty of good Chinese food in New Orleans, and none of them would mistreat their customers like Dian Xin.
Best Chinese food in the quarter. Great food, great prices, and wonderful service. Get the Bao while you’re there.
